Notes: 0 = Disposable cig-a-like devices (single-use device; not rechargeable); 1 = Rechargeable cig-a-like or ?closed tank? devices with single-use e-liquid cartridges (e.g., Blu or Vuse e-cigarettes) ; 2 = Small or mid-sized open-tank/refillable devices like vape pens or Egos; 3 = Large open-tank/refillable devices, mods, or other advanced personal vaporizers; 4 = JUULs; 5 = Any pod-based device other than a JUUL, such as a PHIX or Suorin

ElementDescription: On the days that you use your electronic cigarette or personal vaporizer (e.g., e-cigarettes, vape pens, mods, or pod-based systems like JUUL) to vape nicotine, how many times per day do you usually use it?  Assume that one ?time? consists of around 15 puffs or lasts around 10 minutes.
Which of these statements best describes you? (mark one)
Notes: 1 = I have quit using e-cigarettes/vaping and will never go back.; 2 = I have cut down on or quit my e-cigarette use/vaping, but I still worry about slipping back, so I need to keep working on the changes I have made; 3 = I still use e-cigarettes/vape, but I will begin to change, like cutting back on the amount that I use ; 4 = I definitely plan to change my e-cigarette use/vaping, and I am ready to make some plans about how to change; 5 = I definitely plan to change my e-cigarette use/vaping, but I am not ready to make any plans about how to change; 6 = I often think about changing the way that I use e-cigarettes/vape, but I have not planned to change it yet; 7 = I sometimes think about changing the way that I use e-cigarettes/vape, but I have not planned to change it yet; 8 = I rarely think about changing the way that I use e-cigarettes/vape, and I have no plans to change; 9 = I never think about changing the way that I use e-cigarettes/vape, and I have no plans to change; 10 = I enjoy using e-cigarettes/vaping and have decided never to change it = I have no interest in changing the way that I use e-cigarettes.
